annotationA: Kinesin-like protein at 68D (Klp68D) is the kinesin-2beta motor subunit of the heterotrimeric kinesin-2. Klp68D associates with Klp64D and Kap3. Klp68D plays an essential role in the sensory cilia assembly, microtubule organization in dendrites, and axonal transport
annotationB: Intraflagellar transport 52; It is involved in the biological process described with: cilium morphogenesis; cilium assembly; microtubule-based movement
